race.comment: SIR LAMORAK (1) has been right there in recent efforts and looks to be working up to another victory. Gets a stack of weight relief with the 3kg claim and should be playing a major role in the outcome. PIERRE CARDINNIGAN (6) got the job done at Murwillumbah last time out and winning rider Thornton sticks in the stirrups. Only needs some luck from the wide draw to be fighting out the finish. ICHIBAN (2) has saluted around this circuit and must be respected out of the champion Waller yard. Top-three commodity. Stablemate EMPIRE OF ART (10) doesn't win out of turn but is usually thereabouts and is a must for the multiples. SPILL THE SECRET (7) will gives supporters a sight up on speed.
